## Type Casting

### Widening (Automatic)

Smaller type → Larger type
byte -> short -> int -> float -> long -> double

```java
int num = 10;
long value = num;
double d = value;
```
No data loss.

### Narrowing (Manual)

Larger type → Smaller type

```java
double pi = 9.99;
int x = (int) pi;
```

Output:

```java
9
```
Decimal part is removed.

