## Output in Java

### println()

```java
System.out.println("Hello");
```
Prints text and moves to next line.

### print()

```java
System.out.print("Hello");
```
Prints text without moving to next line.

### printf()

```java
String name = "Tripti";
int age = 21;
System.out.printf("Name: %s, Age: %d%n", name, age);
```

### Format Specifiers

| Specifier | Meaning  |
| --------- | -------- |
| `%d`      | int      |
| `%f`      | double   |
| `%s`      | String   |
| `%c`      | char     |
| `%n`      | New line |

